                 rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000023 ;
                 obo:IAO_0000115 "A soil quality role is a role inherent in a region of relevance reflecting how well a soil, that is part of the bearer, performs the functions of maintaining biodiversity and productivity, partitioning water and solute flow, filtering and buffering, nutrient cycling, and providing support for plants and other structures."@en ;
                 obo:IAO_0000119 "Definition partly adapted from https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soil_quality" ;
                 rdfs:label "soil quality role"@en ;
                 oeo:OEO_00020426 """issue: https://github.com/OpenEnergyPlatform/ontology/issues/1962
pull request: https://github.com/OpenEnergyPlatform/ontology/pull/2006""" .


