                 obo:IAO_0000115 """The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'iron and steel production' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Carbon dioxide is the predominant gas emitted from the production of iron and steel. The sources of the carbon dioxide emissions include that from carbon-containing reducing agents such as coke and pulverized coal, and, from minerals such as limestone and dolomite added.""" ;
                 obo:IAO_0000119 "2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories, Volume 1, Chapter 8.5, https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2006gl/" ;
