                 obo:IAO_0000115 """The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'other process uses of carbonates' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Includes limestone, dolomite and other carbonates etc. Emissions from the use of limestone, dolomite and other carbonates should be included in the industrial source category where they are emitted. Therefore, for example, where a carbonate is used as a flux for iron and steel production, resultant emissions should be reported under 2C1 “Iron and Steel Production” rather than this
subcategory.""" ;
                 obo:IAO_0000119 "2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories, Volume 1, Chapter 8.5, https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2006gl/" ;
                 rdfs:label "CRF sector (IPCC 2006): other process uses of carbonates"@en ;
                 oeo:OEO_00010037 "CRF 2.A.4" ;
