###  https://openenergyplatform.org/ontology/oeo/OEO_00010344
oeo:OEO_00010344 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                          oeo:OEO_00000227 ;
                 obo:BFO_0000050 oeo:OEO_00010166 ;
                 oeo:OEO_00000504 oeo:OEO_00000242 ;
                 obo:IAO_0000115 """The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'ammonia' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Ammonia (NH3) is a major industrial chemical and the most important nitrogenous material produced. Ammonia gas is used directly as a fertilizer, in heat treating, paper pulping, nitric acid and nitrates manufacture, nitric acid ester and nitro compound manufacture, explosives of various types, and as a refrigerant. Amines, amides, and miscellaneous other organic compounds, such as urea, are made from ammonia. The main greenhouse gas emitted from NH3 production is CO2. CO2 used in the production of urea, a downstream process, should be subtracted from the CO2 generated and accounted for in the AFOLU Sector.""" ;
                 obo:IAO_0000119 "2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories, Volume 1, Chapter 8.5, https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2006gl/" ;
                 rdfs:label "CRF sector (IPCC 2006): ammonia production"@en ;
                 oeo:OEO_00010037 "CRF 2.B.1" ;
                 oeo:OEO_00020426 """issue: https://github.com/OpenEnergyPlatform/ontology/issues/1401
