                 oeo:OEO_00000504 oeo:OEO_00000242 ;
                 obo:IAO_0000115 """The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'nitric acid production' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Nitric acid is used as a raw material mainly in the manufacture of nitrogenous-based fertiliser. Nitric acid may also be used in the production of adipic acid and explosives (e.g., dynamite), for metal etching and in the processing of ferrous metals. The main greenhouse gas emitted from HNO3 production is nitrous oxide""" ;
                 obo:IAO_0000119 "2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories, Volume 1, Chapter 8.5, https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2006gl/" ;
                 rdfs:label "CRF sector (IPCC 2006): nitric acid production"@en ;
                 oeo:OEO_00010037 "CRF 2.B.2" ;
